definition.value: Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of head.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of liver.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of lung.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of neck.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of chest.
The X-ray examination of the lower limbs of the body.
The radiographic examination of the tracheobronchial tree following the injection of a radiopaque material.
The radiographic examination of the bile ducts after a contrast medium has been injected.
A radiographic procedure to obtain an image of the urinary bladder by filling the bladder with contrast medium.

A type of radiography used specifically to examine breast tissue. The procedure utilizes a low-dose of x-rays or radiation to generate an image. A mammography exam or mammogram, is used as a screening tool to detect early breast cancer in women experiencing no symptoms and to detect and diagnose breast disease.

The radiographic examination of the spinal cord and nerve roots following the injection of a contrast medium into the spinal subarachnoid space. The X-rays taken may highlight conditions such as spinal tumors, spinal cord swelling and herniated discs.
A radiologic test that involves the examination of the entire body in a single procedure.
A radiographic examination of the vagina using the intravaginal injection of contrast medium.
Any surgical procedure conducted on the cardiovascular system.
A surgery that fixes or mends heart.
Treatment to correct or improve vision.
Use of glasses to correct vision.
Any surgical procedure conducted on the nasolacrimal duct.
A surgical procedure to correct strabismus in the eye.

value.value: The ketogenic diet is a high-fat, low-carbohydrate, adequate-protein diet that mimics a fasting state, resulting in the substitution of ketone bodies as a source of energy. The ketogenic diet can be used to reduce recurrent epileptic seizures in individuals with intractable epilepsy. Intractable epilepsy is defined as epilepsy that failed to respond to three or more antiepileptic drugs.
Texture-modified foods and thickened drinks used to reduce the risks of choking and aspiration for individuals with oropharyngeal incoordination or dysphagia.

Supplementation of uncooked cornstarch intended to prevent hepatomegaly and hypoglycemia, typically for individuals with irregular hepatic glycogen storage. Supplementation can include both regular cornstarch and extended release cornstarch.

definition.value: Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of manus.
A procedure whre the radiographic film or sensor is placed inside the mouth and uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of teeth and other oral structures.
A technique to visualize the blood vessels in the back of the eye by injecting fluorescent dye and then imaging it.

A visualization of the fundus of the eye including the retina and optic nerve with a fundoscope, a device that projects light through the pupil of the eye and visualizes the fundus with magnification.
A quantitative measurement of a particular hormone present in a blood sample.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of pes.
Analysis of a cerebrospinal fluid sample.
Use of an imaging test that uses small amounts of radiation to produce pictures of shoulder.
A direct appraisal of a patient's condition by a dentist that is based on an oral exam, medical history, and the patient's account of symptoms.
A direct appraisal by a professional who is an expert in premature babies or newborns with high-risk or complex health conditions. The physician performs a physical exam and takes medical history.
Measurement of the functionality of an enzyme.
A test that measures all areas of your eyesight including peripheral vision.
A medical examination performed using of magnetic resonance imaging to image the spinal cord.
A test to determine the smallest letters a patient can clearly see.

Microscopic examination of the hair (also called hair microscopy) is an inexpensive tool that may aid in the diagnosis of systemic disorders as the appearance, structure, and/or growth of hair are modified in various congenital and acquired diseases. (PMID:34843009)
Measurement of the functionality of an enzyme derived from leukocytes.
Measurement of the functionality of an enzyme derived from erythrocytes.
Measurement of the functionality of an enzyme derived from a particular tissue
A test that measures the ability of the blood to bind iron.
A quantitative measurement of metabolites present in a particular tissue.
A type of CT where the image resolution is enhanced to look at lung disease.
A test that measures DNA damage/breakage in patient cells.  DNA damage repair plays an important role in cancer initiation and progression, and in therapeutic resistance.
A quantitative measurement of immunoglobulins present in a blood sample.

label.value: blood gas assessment in umbilical cord blood

definition.value: A test that measures the amount of oxygen, carbon dioxide, and pH in the blood of the umbilical cord.

This test is used to measure the amount of L-Selectin (CD62L) shed from the surface of neutrophils before and after stimulation of the TLR pathway. The test can help identify patients with defects in their toll-like receptor signalling pathway and can be used to diagnose IRAK-4, MyD88 and UNC93B deficiency. (NHS)
A quantitative measurement of metabolites present in a cerebrospinal fluid sample.
The time an indigestible, non-absorbable markers takes to be excreted.
A quantitative measurement of xenobiotics (a chemical foreign to the body) present in a stool sample.
